problems.teacher_notes:
#markdown
This problem is a bit harder, in that it requires students to consider if-else possibility. Students may want check a range of values. This is possible by either using and AND statement (we haven't done this yet), or nested if statements (we haven't done that either).

### AND statement

```norun;
if (temp > 30) {
  Esplora.writeRGB(255, 0, 0);
}
if (temp > 18 && temp <= 30) {
  Esplora.writeRGB(0, 255, 0);
}
if (temp <= 18) {
  Esplora.writeRGB(0, 0, 255);
}
```
This is a completely valid solution, and students should be encouraged to experiment with concepts they haven't been taught yet. However, understanding how the else-if works makes it easier:

```norun;
if (temp > 30) {
  // This part checks the range above 30
  Esplora.writeRGB(255, 0, 0);
}
else if (temp > 18) {
  // This checks the range 19-30 because of the else-if
  Esplora.writeRGB(0, 255, 0);
}
else {
  // checks 18 and below
  Esplora.writeRGB(0, 0, 255);
}
```
Students will be forced to understand that the `else` catches everything *else* in order to complete this question.

